textAfterTable: 2012: One-year letterwinner ... expected to see plenty of action as a slotback and as the team's primary backup quarterback. 2011: Played in nine contests as a reserve slotback ... rushed 14 times for 63 yards and caught five passes for 44 yards ... also had five kickoff returns for 95 yards (19.0 avg) and threw one incompletion ... rushed three times for 20 yards and caught one pass for three yards in a 63-0 win over Guilford (10/1) ... had two catches for 21 yards in a 17-14 win at Emory & Henry (10/8). 2010: Saw action in four games as a backup quarterback ... rushed twice for 16 yards and completed his only pass for a 6-yard gain ... had a 13-yard rush in a 45-3 win over Juniata (11/13). High School: Earned two letters each as a member of the football and baseball teams at Benet Academy. Personal: Father, Paul, played quarterback at Washington University ... uncle, Mike, played linebacker at Northern Illinois and is a member of the school's Hall of Fame ... European history major.
